Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This report concludes retrospectively on circumstantial evidence
that EBLV-2 infection had been contracted by the deceased Swiss
researcher in Finland and not in Switzerland as previously supposed.
EBLV-2 infection has also been responsible for human deaths in other
areas (namely the UK) where classical carnivore-transmitted rabies is
absent -- see ProMED-mail references below.

A photograph of a Daubenton's bat (_Myotis daubentonii_) in flight
can be accessed at
<http://www.nhm.ac.uk/nature-online/species-of-the-day/biodiversity/loss-of-habitat/myotis-daubentonii/index.html>.

The HealthMap/ProMED-mail interactive map of Finland is available at
<http://healthmap.org/r/08L4>. - Mod.CP]
